attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, SPARC, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib/ld-uClibc.so.0, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The analyzed MIPS32 binary is an IoT botnet variant, likely belonging to the Mirai or Gafgyt families. It exhibits several high-confidence malicious behaviors: persistence via the creation of an init script at '/etc/init.d/xs.main', process enumeration and cloaking using '/proc/%s/cmdline' and 'prctl', and remote payload acquisition via busybox utilities (wget, curl, tftp). The binary contains hardcoded HTTP request templates (GET, POST, HEAD) with spoofed User-Agents for C2 communication and potential DDoS functionality. Relevant IOCs include the persistence path '/etc/init.d/xs.main', the executable path '/var/main', and the remote resource strings '/cat.sh' and '/mipsel'.
